results.description: Whilst strolling through the grounds of Penang Botanical Gardens in Malaysia, I was keeping my wits about me and a hand on my gear. The local monkeys are very cheeky and have developed a taste for shiny valuables; which they will then trade back in return for food! Whilst scanning my surroundings I noticed a group of monkeys moving slower than the others, higher up on a set of power lines. Then I spotted the small orange/gold baby and started shooting instantly. So here we have a family of Dusky Leaf Monkeys checking me out warily.
